<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>KBCorp Food Inventory</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles-project5.css">
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Bebas+Neue&family=Montserrat:wght@400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0-beta3/css/all.min.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <a href="/" class="logo">
        <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/kibrsifr/NodeJS-Portfolio-Website/main/resources/logoheader.png" alt="KBCORP PORTFOLIO Logo">
        </a>
        <nav>
        <a href="/projects">Projects</a>
        </nav>
        
    </header>

    <div class="main-content">
        <div class="text-content">
            <h1>The KBCorp Food Inventory System</h1>
            <p>This web application helps you manage your food inventory easily using CRUD operations. You can add food items and enter details like ingredients, stock, dishes sold, and prices.</p>

            <p>The system automatically calculates the total profit based on the number of dishes sold and their prices. It uses MongoDB, which will set up a database for you automatically.</p>
            
            <p>Just make sure MongoDB is turned on for everything to work smoothly.</p>
            
        </div>
        
        <div class="section">
            <div class="button-container">
                
                <form action="/search" method="GET">
                    <input type="text" name="query" placeholder="Search by food item">
                    <button type="submit">Search</button>
                    <div>
                    <a href="/add" class="btn">Add Food Item</a>
                    </div>
                </form>
            </div>
            
            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Food Item</th>
                        <th>Ingredients</th>
                        <th>Stock</th>
                        <th>Sold Dishes</th>
                        <th>Price</th>
                        <th>Actions</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <% if (foodItems && foodItems.length > 0) { %>
                        <% foodItems.forEach(item => { %>
                            <tr>
                                <td><%= item.name %></td>
                                <td><%= item.ingredients.join(', ') %></td>
                                <td><%= item.stock %></td>
                                <td><%= item.soldDishes %></td>
                                <td>$<%= item.price.toFixed(2) %></td>
                                <td class="actions">
                                    <a href="/edit/<%= item._id %>" class="btn">Edit</a>
                                    <a href="/delete/<%= item._id %>" class="btn">Delete</a>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                        <% }) %>
                    <% } else { %>
                        <tr>
                            <td colspan="6">No food items found.</td>
                        </tr>
                    <% } %>
                </tbody>
            </table>
            
            <% if (grossProfit !== undefined) { %>
                <div class="gross-profit">
                    Total Profit: $<%= grossProfit.toFixed(2) %>
                </div>
            <% } %>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
